  "prompt": "Is it true that we fantasize about friends of opposite gender?",
  "response": "Many people do experience fantasies about friends of the opposite gender. This can be influenced by various factors, including emotional connections, attraction, shared interests, and social dynamics. Such fantasies can range from mild daydreams to more intense thoughts and can occur in the context of close friendships. \n\nHowever, the prevalence and nature of these fantasies can vary widely among individuals based on personality, relationship status, and social context. It's also important to note that having fantasies doesn't necessarily mean that one desires to act on them or that it will affect the friendship negatively. Communication and boundaries are key in maintaining healthy relationships, especially when feelings or attractions may arise.",
